article.headline: North Florida 95, Campbell 84
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Alain Laroche scored 23 points to lead North Florida to a 95-84 win over Campbell University Thursday. Freshman Ryan Daugherty added 18 points and eight rebounds for North Florida (4-12, 1-8). Rashad Williams had 17 points and Christ Timberlake had 12. Eric Smith led Campbell (5-11, 4-5) with 19 points, and Maurice Latham and Reggie Bishop each scored 15. Comerlee Poole and Ruell Pringle scored 11 each for Campbell. North Florida led by 12 at the half, 48-36. The team scored on 56 percent (18-of-32) of its field goal attempts in the first half and 62 percent (13-of-21) in the second. From the free-throw line, North Florida went 6-of-10 in the first half and 18-of-24 in the second. Campbell shot 15-of-29 from the field in the first half and 17-of-40 in the second. The team went 2-of-12 from the line in the first half and 12-of-16 in the second.
